			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="406">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Karen Vogel&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4715">The First Year</a>&rdquo; [October 2012] just about made me cry. The scene where her friend tells her that &ldquo;there must not be anything like being a mother&rdquo; would have meant nothing to me seven months ago, before I became a mother myself. I live in Spain, an ocean away from my own mother, and only after becoming a parent did I even begin to understand how my mom must feel when she&rsquo;s standing in her kitchen, talking on the phone with me, and how difficult it has been for her to see her daughter move so far away.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Dusty Gammons<br>Madrid<br />Spain</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

